<h2>How to Calculate Your Local SEO ROI Step by Step</h2>
<p>ROI calculation for local SEO is straightforward once you have the right data. The formula is:</p>
<p><strong>ROI = (Revenue from SEO - Cost of SEO) / Cost of SEO x 100</strong></p>
<p>Here is how to apply it with real numbers.</p>
<h3>Step 1: Track Revenue from SEO</h3>
<p>You need to know exactly how much revenue comes from organic search. Set up the following tracking systems:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> with conversion goals tied to form submissions, phone calls, and appointment bookings</li>
<li><strong>Call tracking numbers</strong> on your website and Google Business Profile to attribute phone leads to SEO</li>
<li><strong>Customer relationship management</strong> tags that mark leads as "organic search" in your pipeline</li>
<li><strong>Revenue attribution</strong> that connects closed deals back to their original traffic source</li>
</ul>
<p>For local businesses, the simplest approach is to ask every new customer: "How did you find us?" Record the answer in your customer database. Over time, this produces an accurate picture of SEO-driven revenue.</p>
<h3>Step 2: Calculate Total SEO Costs</h3>
